AB  - In modern warfare, electromagnetic dominance serves as a prerequisite for air and maritime dominance. Accurately recognizing the modulation types of enemy communication and radar signals is fundamental to implementing electronic reconnaissance, jamming, and anti-jamming. Rapid identification of modulation types for unknown signals enables judgment of enemy equipment models and tactical intentions, providing critical intelligence for command decisions. Different modulation signals require distinct jamming strategies, and identification errors may lead to jamming failure or even exposure of friendly positions. Combined with the digital twin framework, this paper designs an OMFCTCT network to identify and classify down-modulated signals in complex environments. Experimental results show that the recognition accuracy of this method is improved compared with some existing methods. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
