AB  - The Osaka Wangan Expressway Western Extension Project (OWEWE Project) is a 14.5 km long bypass project that is part of the Osaka Bay Road. This four-tower continuous cable-stayed bridge is part of the OWEWE project and will be a 2.8 km long, 6-lane bridge connecting Port Island and Rokko Island in Kobe. The planned structure features three suspended spans 653m in length and will be the longest of its type in the world. This paper gives an overview of the project and presents the planning concept, structural features of this bridge, seismic design, and wind resistant design. © 2025 IABSE Symposium Tokyo 2025: Environmentally Friendly Technologies and Structures: Focusing on Sustainable Approaches - Report All rights reserved.
