TI  - A Multimedia Digital Twin-Driven Intelligent Compression Method
PY  - 2025
T2  - 2025 17th International Conference on Wireless Communications and Signal Processing, WCSP 2025
DO  - 10.1109/WCSP68525.2025.1010587
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105033640161?origin=resultslist
AB  - To address the limited adaptability of conventional multimedia compression techniques across diverse application scenarios, this paper proposes an intelligent compression method based on Digital Twin technology. The method first utilizes a comprehensive set of influence factors, covering source, channel, terminal, and content dimensions, to perform a parametrized profiling of the application scenario, thereby constructing its digital twin model. Subsequently, a preliminary filtering of algorithm branches is conducted via a multimedia algorithm search tree, followed by a fine-grained decision-making process driven by a weight-based decision algorithm. This algorithm evaluates the features obtained from the Digital Twin model through weight filtering and weighted calculation, ultimately recommending the optimal compression algorithm and parameter combination. Experimental results demonstrate that the proposed method can provide efficient and adaptive compression solutions for various scenarios, including indoor, outdoor, and mobile environments. © 2025 IEEE.
