AB  - Digital twins are virtual counterparts of physical systems, crucial for monitoring and reasoning in cyber-physical systems. Implementing a Digital Twin requires a language specification for ensuring interpretability and interoperability among integrated systems. Ontologies from various domains can address syntactic and semantic inter-operability issues. To support global communication and knowledge exchange, mechanisms for system integration are needed. This paper pro-poses a model-based approach for automatically generating a modular multimodal core ontology specific to a port Digital Twin. The approach involves stablishing syntactic and semantic alignments between on tologies using various algorithms, followed by are factoring step to unify concepts for the domain. Finally, reasoning services are applied to verify the consistency of the generated on tologies. © The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Singapore Pte Ltd. 2026.
