DO  - 10.1080/0305215X.2025.2581132
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105022287668?origin=resultslist
AB  - Wiring is a common activity in electrical device manufacturing. Wiring planning includes planning the path along which the wire is placed and determining wire and port connection order. The current study presents an integrated method for the automation of robotic wiring planning. The novelty of the method lies in forming a fully automated planning layer between product design documentation and wiring execution using a digital twin. The plans are devised based on data extracted from product design documents. A linear programming model following robotic wiring constraints was developed for finding optimal paths. A heuristic combined with dynamic programming was developed to determine feasible wire and port order. The method was tested with small, medium and large panels with different layouts. Optimal wiring paths with a feasible high-quality wire and port order were found. The method offers a solution for robotic wiring planning with optimal paths and a feasible order in reasonable computation times. © 2025 The Author(s). Published by Informa UK Limited, trading as Taylor & Francis Group.
