AB  - Differential relays are essential for protecting transmission lines, but their reliance on communication networks makes them vulnerable to cyberattacks, especially false data injection attacks (FDIAs). This paper explores how such attacks can be exploited and proposes a detection method to distinguish attacks from internal faults. The proposed approach compares positive-sequence voltage measurements at the relay terminal with estimates from two observers, each based on state-space models (for healthy and faulty conditions) using both local and remote inputs. Under normal or fault scenarios, one observer's estimate matches the measured voltage, reflecting the true system state. In contrast, during an FDIA, both observers deviate, leading to noticeable mismatches. Simulation results on the IEEE 39-bus system demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method in identifying FDIAs.  © 2025 IEEE.
