AB  - Frequent extreme disasters threaten the operational security of cyber-physical distribution systems. To enhance post-disaster power supply and recovery efficiency, this paper proposes an isolated microgrid partitioning optimization framework based on coupled energy-information flows. First, a communication network model is developed to integrate intelligent terminal devices, incorporating constraints on communication data volume, link bandwidth, and terminal computational capacity. Next, a multi-type emergency resource scheduling model coordinates the spatiotemporal dispatch of mobile communication vehicles and repair crews for emergency communication support and fault restoration. Building on this foundation, a coupled cyber-physical partitioning model dynamically integrates distribution and communication networks, leveraging grid-forming power sources and intelligent terminals. An improved IEEE 33-bus case verifies the method, demonstrating how energy-information coupling accelerates load recovery and mitigates outage-related losses.  © 2025 IEEE.
