AB  - With the accelerated development of smart campus construction, Internet of Things (IoT) devices, intelligent terminals, and core network facilities have been deeply integrated into teaching and management scenarios. Technologies such as 5G, AI, and edge computing have improved campus management efficiency but also brought new security threats, such as device heterogeneity and data centralization. Attack targets have expanded from traditional servers to edge nodes such as cameras and access control systems. To address these issues, this paper proposes a multi-technology collaborative security framework for smart campuses. It ensures data trustworthiness through blockchain, implements dynamic authorization with zero trust, and forms a hybrid virtual-physical drill mechanism using AI and digital twins to simulate new types of attacks. This paper proposes a theoretical framework that integrates blockchain, AI, and digital twins, providing a conceptual foundation for addressing dynamic threats and privacy issues in smart campuses. © 2025 IEEE.
