UR  - https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105011681121?origin=resultslist
AB  - To partially resolve the problems existing in the hull structural condition monitoring, this paper carries out a study of ship structural strength digital twin. Specifically, a stress amplification coefficient method is put forward, which can fulfill the rapid cognition and assessment of the overall structural state for any typical hull structure. This paper first chose the three-compartment model of a super large container ship as the object of study, and then designed 6 representative application conditions to account for the usage effect of the presented methodology. Related studies show that if there is no coupling between the loadings on the hull structure, the presented methodology has an excellent usage effect. However, if there is a coupling between the loadings, the usage effect of the presented methodology is relatively poor. But by improving the methodology for loading recognition accordingly, the actual usage effect of the presented methodology will be greatly enhanced. © 2025 Informa UK Limited, trading as Taylor & Francis Group.
