AB  - A substantial part of the waterway infrastructure built in Europe after World War II, such as locks, quay walls, and coastal protection structures, is coming to the end of its useful life and will either need to be replaced or fundamentally repaired in the next few years. The use of digital twins, which will revolutionize civil engineering in the next 1-3 years, offers enormous opportunities for the complete digitalization of assets and promotes more efficient structural inspections and maintenance processes. Damage models and inspection results can be efficiently shared with the planning civil engineers through the cloud portal without any loss of information. This paper presents methods and solutions for data acquisition, evaluation, and provision of the data sets that were developed as part of two research projects 3D HydroMapper and port_AI in Germany from 2018 to 2024.  © 2020 ASCE.
