AB  - The application of Digital Twin technology in high-speed railway stations is becoming increasingly widespread, providing new opportunities for the intelligent development of high-speed railway stations. This paper takes Guangzhou Baiyun High-speed Railway Station as an example to explore the integrated design and implementation of a Digital Twin-based smart high-speed railway station in depth. It elaborates on how to construct an accurate Digital Twin model, covering various aspects such as station facilities and train operation. By implementing a real-time synchronization and information integration between the Digital Twin model and physical entities through “Train - Station - Thing - Person” entity models, the paper discusses the design and implementation of application functions in passenger services, equipment maintenance, and emergency management. It also explores how Digital Twin technology can enhance the operational efficiency, service quality, and safety of high-speed railway stations, providing comprehensive theoretical support and practical references for the construction of smart high-speed railway stations. © 2025 SPIE.
