AB  - To tackle challenges in large-scale, order-intensive weaving workshops, an intelligent scheduling method integrating digital twin technology was proposed. By establishing virtual-physical mapping, the method enables real-time monitoring and visualization of the weaving process to provide real-time data for production scheduling. Then, a multi-objective scheduling model is developed to minimize delay time, energy consumption, and loom changeovers, incorporating AGV transport time. An enhanced discrete Jaya algorithm (UPG-Jaya) is introduced for optimization. The new algorithm is demonstrated and tested with large-scale scenarios (500×2291). Experimental results show that the proposed algorithm can find a better solution with reducing order delays, saving energy and improving resource utilization. Additionally, a digital twin-based production scheduling system is developed to support the intelligent transformation of textile enterprises.  © 2025 IEEE.
