AB  - In response to the demand for dynamic monitoring of carbon emissions during the construction phase, an intelligent monitoring system based on the Internet of Things (IoT) has been designed. The system is built on the framework of Cyber-Physical Systems (CPS), utilizing vibration sensors, energy consumption monitoring terminals, and RFID identification devices to dynamically collect data on the operational parameters of construction machinery, energy consumption, and the circulation information of building materials. A Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) neural network is employed to construct a carbon emission prediction model. Application examples demonstrate that the system can accurately identify concrete pouring as the core source of carbon emissions, achieving a monthly reduction of 18.5 tons of carbon dioxide equivalent through equipment optimization. © 2025 SPIE. All rights reserved.
