AB  - As one of the core technologies of Industry 4.0, digital twins have gradually been applied to actual production processes. This paper proposes and designs a digital twin-driven intelligent manufacturing system solution, aiming to optimize the control and management of production lines through the integration of virtual and real-world elements. The system integrates modules for robot operations, CNC machining, and AGV transportation, and employs advanced industrial protocols such as MQTT, OPC UA, and ModbusTCP to achieve efficient data transmission and scheduling control between devices. Experimental verification has shown that the system excels in multi-station collaboration, integration of heterogeneous equipment, and multi-module coupling and cooperation, significantly enhancing the efficiency and flexibility of production lines. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
