AB  - Marine evaporation duct inversion is critical for maritime communication and radar monitoring, yet faces challenges in integrating multi-source environmental data and expert knowledge. This paper proposes a knowledge graph-driven cognitive digital twin (CDT) framework to enable intelligent inversion of marine evaporation ducts. The system integrates an ontology layer for formalizing atmospheric physics rules, a knowledge layer for real-time assimilation of oceanographic sensor data, and a cognitive layer embedding our novel RGCN-PRotatE reasoning model. Validated on evaporation duct monitoring scenarios, the framework demonstrates 19% accuracy gain in inversion parameters and 73.4% reliability in decision recommendations, providing human operators with physics-aware inversion guidance. © 2025 IEEE.
