AB  - Testing, Inspection, and Certification (TIC) in the maritime sector is evolving rapidly to accommodate the growing complexity of digital technologies, strict environmental regulations, and the increasing demand for operational efficiency. This paper proposes an Integrated Maritime TIC Enterprise Architecture that leverages Artificial Intelligence (AI), Blockchain, and Robotics to deliver a more resilient and transparent mar-itime ecosystem. Drawing upon recent scholarly contributions in maritime communication networks, blockchain-based mar-itime supply chains, and enterprise architecture frameworks, we identify critical gaps and challenges in existing TIC practices. Our proposed architecture adopts a layered approach-ranging from Presentation to Integration and Data layers-and addresses the end-to-end needs of stakeholders such as ship owners, classification societies, port authorities, and regulatory bodies. By unifying edge intelligence, big data analytics, digital twins, and blockchain smart contracts, the architecture offers robust data governance, enhanced security, and efficient workflow orchestration for maritime stakeholders. We also examine how AIdriven predictive maintenance, robotic inspection systems, and integrated 6G maritime networks can be aligned with enterprise architecture principles to ensure scalability and future readiness. The paper concludes with a discussion on the potential impact of this framework in fostering safer maritime operations, reduced downtime, and more transparent compliance, thereby shaping the next generation of maritime innovation.  © 2025 IEEE.
