AB  - This study presents a control method for distribution automation terminals based on Digital Twin technology, aiming to overcome the shortcomings of traditional approaches, such as inflexible logic and delayed responses in dynamic power grid environments. The method leverages real-time virtual modeling to achieve comprehensive monitoring, dynamic analysis, and intelligent control. Key contributions include equipment status monitoring and feature extraction, fault prognosis combining matter-element extension and fuzzy clustering, and adaptive response mechanisms driven by predictive analytics. Comparative experiments validate the method's effectiveness, demonstrating significant improvements in response speed and operational reliability. Challenges related to data security and model accuracy are also discussed, highlighting avenues for future research. © 2025 IEEE.
