AB  - The increasing automation of maritime ports introduces complex cybersecurity challenges that conventional industrial control system protections fail to address. This paper proposes a cybersecurity framework for automated ports integrating real-time anomaly detection, adaptive risk scoring, and safety-constrained response optimization. The system demonstrates 92.7% detection rates and 2.3% false positive rate, enabled by continuous Bayesian updates and quantile regression. Results validate effective protection for port automation systems against evolving cyber-physical threats without disrupting critical operations. © 2025 IEEE.
