AB  - The distributed photovoltaic grid-connected voltage level is low, and the dispatching does not master its operation information, which brings great safety risks to the stable operation of the power grid. In view of these problems, the communication fusion network scheme for the whole county distributed photovoltaic cluster access is put forward. This scheme conducts quantitative evaluation of multi-mode communication technology for optical fiber communication, wireless private network, wireless public network, and power line carrier communication through four dimensions, that is service classification, network performance index, economic cost of network construction, technology maturity and industry chain. A prototype prototype based on flexible access based on distributed PV was developed and tested in the laboratory. This scheme effectively improves the communication access, carrying capacity and security protection capability of distributed photovoltaic, and provides theoretical basis and technical support for distributed photovoltaic communication networking, network security, edge terminal deployment and cluster control. ©2024 IEEE.
