AB  - In Digital Twin (DT) assisted Intelligent Transportation Systems (ITS), cloud servers can use data from vehicle sensors to construct DT replicas of road scenes and utilize this these for tracking, replicating, and predicting traffic environments. To support these applications, the DT of ITS should be accurately constructed in real time. However, due to the limited computation of vehicles and communication resource of Internet of Vehicle (IoV), reconstruction in local vehicles or cloud server would arouse a large delay. Therefore, we propose to jointly train a point cloud reconstruction network on the vehicle, Roadside Units (RSU) and cloud server, and the cloud aggregates the network parameters of the three terminals to obtain a global network. To be more specific, an optimization problem is formulated to minimize the reconstruction delay by joinly adjusting communication and computation resources allocations. An alternating optimization based algorithm named as TRA is proposed to achieve the suboptimal solutions. Finally, extensive simulations are carried out to show that the TRA schemes obtained by this algorithm are superior to other baselines. © 2024 IEEE.
