AB  - To partially resolve the problems existing in the condition monitoring of hull structures, this paper put forward a stress amplification coefficient method, which can fulfill the rapid cognition and assessment of the structural stress state in the hull structural region of concern. Specifically, this paper first chose the three-compartment model of a super-large container ship as the object of study, and then designed 6 representative application cases to account for the actual usage effect of the presented methodology. Related studies show that when there is no coupling between the actual loads suffered by the hull structure, the presented methodology has a good application effect. However, when coupling exists, the application effect of the method presented in this paper is relatively poor. © 2024 by the International Society of Offshore and Polar Engineers (ISOPE).
