AB  - This paper investigates the application of Digital Twin (DT) technology to enhance efficiency and intelligence in manufacturing, particularly within machine tool processing lines. DT seamlessly integrates physical and virtual systems, enabling realtime simulation, monitoring, and optimization of manufacturing operations. The proposed system features multi-axis motion control, real-time data collection, and simulation, structured in three layers: the physical layer (hardware), the DT engine (data and computation), and the virtual model (3D simulation). Key components such as intelligent warehousing, Automated Guided Vehicles (AGVs), and Radio Frequency Identification(RFID) technology automate material handling, reduce manual labor, and streamline material flow. The paper further discusses the hardware and software frameworks, with Plant Simulation used for process design and performance prediction through fuzzy neural networks. Ultimately, DT integration facilitates real-time monitoring, process optimization, and enhances the development of smart factories.  © 2024 IEEE.
