AB  - Active distribution networks are typical cyber-physical systems, where faults in the cyber system may trigger voltage violations, and uncertainties of renewable energy in the physical system may lead to voltage fluctuations. In light of this, a multi-level voltage/var stochastic optimization method for distribution networks considering communication conditions is proposed. The proposed method achieves optimal coordination of inverters with different communication conditions under the renewable energy uncertainty. In the central level, a stochastic optimization problem is formulated by optimizing the output of inverters with normal communication, which achieves optimal coordination in mathematical form with inverters suffering communication interruption. It is noted that, at the central level, decisions are made for inverters with normal communication, which consider the local adjustment model for inverter suffering communication interruption. At the local level, local terminal decides whether to follow the decisions made at the central level or locally adjust output of inverters based on communication states and voltage violation states. The proposed method is validated in modified IEEE 33-node distribution network. © 2024 IEEE.
