AB  - This paper presents a machine learning-based approach for estimating sloshing activity in a liquefied natural gas (LNG) tank using several measurable inputs, such as sea states and ship accelerations. The proposed method involves training a model from experimental data and using it to estimate sloshing activity in real-life situations. The trained model acts as a digital twin of the ship's behavior with respect to sloshing. By estimating sloshing activity based on real ship conditions, rather than relying on conservative assumptions, more accurate risk monitoring is possible, enabling actions to avoid sloshing or plan tank maintenance at the most appropriate time. © 2023 by the International Society of Offshore and Polar Engineers (ISOPE).
