AB  - With the widespread deployment of intelligent communication, computing and control facilities in the power grid, new cyber security risks have been introduced into the power system. In order to prevent network attacks from damaging the power system, a security protection algorithm based on semantic analysis is proposed in this paper. Aiming at the information interaction between terminals, a random subset hash algorithm Authentication algorithm considering time validity is proposed, which can analyze the characteristics of mutual coupling and correlation in the physical space of power grid information network, and detect the consistency and rationality of monitoring information and control instructions. The performance of the algorithm against brute force attack, dictionary attack, denial of service and other attacks is analyzed based on practical network security examples, and the effectiveness of the algorithm in protecting CPS network security is verified.  © 2023 IEEE.
