AB  - This paper presents a review of the research progresses in the design principles and criteria of ships and offshore structures achieved in IACS, IMO and ISO/TC8 in the past several years, with consideration of the development of new rules and guidelines of IACS members and structural safety regulations of regional maritime authorities. The influences of digital twin, operation data, reliability, risk assessment, and human factors in the design on the structural design criteria are discussed. Eventually the suggestions on the development direction of future maritime regulations are given. © 2023 China Ship Scientific Research Center. All rights reserved.
