AB  - A comparative study of cyber security vulnerabilities in ECDIS systems that are implemented on board of three training ships is presented. The cyber security vulnerabilities have been detected by performing computational testing of the ECDIS systems using a widely used vulnerability scanning software tool. The tested ECDIS systems were chosen from different manufacturers and different underlaying operating systems. The results obtained suggest that the selection of the underlying operating system plays an important role in securing the ECDIS systems. In addition, the results point that the cyber security of ECDIS systems could be significantly violated by exploitation of vulnerabilities in the third-party components of ECDIS software. © 2022 IAMUC. All Rights Reserved.
