AB  - Water provisioning is a critical public service that has a direct impact on the welfare and security of the population. Modern water supply infrastructures are complex cyber-physical systems that involve physical equivalents (e.g. pipes, pumps, containers, treatment stations, etc.) as well as automation and monitoring devices. The main challenges for such a system are: uninterrupted supply of quality water, optimal distribution of water reserves and efficient use of existing resources. Anomaly detection in water supply infrastructures is an important aspect that influences the proper functioning and the security of the entire system. As such infrastructures become more and more complex, anomaly detection must be performed in an automated way. But, making the difference between a normal and an abnormal behavior is not a simple task; it requires machine learning (ML) techniques and artificial intelligence (AI) algorithms. This paper presents an automated method of selecting and tuning the best AI model that has the ability to classify the input data as normal or abnormal.  © 2021 IEEE.
